    "Therefore, the key to the recommendation problem is to enable LLMs to effectively utilize the information within the limited context [78,167], and a suitable context length selection for LLMs as recommender systems is worthy of deep consideration.",
    "Observations on Recommendations w.r.t.",
    "Four Aspects of LLMs• As for the public availability, closed-source models generally outperform the opensource models in the recommendation performance, but have poorer flexibility.",
    "• As for the model architecture, different frameworks are adapted to different recommendation tasks and fine-tuning strategies, while LLMs with the casual decoder architecture are still mainstream.",
    "• As for the parameter scale, the larger the parameter scale, the better the recommendation performance."
